text: A hidden gem in this quiet neighborhood. Delicious homemade cakes, flavours change every weekend depending on baker's whim & inspiration. Flavour today: butter cake with a well-browned crispy top. No walk-in, by invitation only.

No regrets accepting the invitation to this rare hideout. Cosy place to dine in. The aroma of fresh bakes fills the place and is a constant surprise to await what’s served next. Can’t think of a better way to spend a leisurely Sunday afternoon. Looking forward to what else the baker has up her sleeve.
Five stars for hospitality. Dangerously delicious coffee by a bjj practitioner. Try at your risk!
